    <item>
      <title>Council Meeting Schedule</title>
      <link>http://localhost:49902/government/meetings/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 01 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:49902/government/meetings/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The Village of Consort Council holds regular meetings to conduct municipal business, make decisions on community matters, and address resident concerns. All meetings are open to the public, and we encourage residents to attend and participate in local democracy.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;regular-meeting-schedule&#34;&gt;Regular Meeting Schedule&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Regular Council Meetings&lt;/strong&gt;: [Day of month, e.g., Second Tuesday] of each month&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;strong&gt;Time&lt;/strong&gt;: [Time, e.g., 7:00 PM]&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;: Village Office Council Chambers, [Address], Consort, AB&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;2025-meeting-dates&#34;&gt;2025 Meeting Dates&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;January [Date], 2025&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;February [Date], 2025&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;March [Date], 2025&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;April [Date], 2025&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;May [Date], 2025&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;June [Date], 2025&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;July [Date], 2025&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;August [Date], 2025&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;September [Date], 2025&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;October [Date], 2025&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;November [Date], 2025&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;December [Date], 2025&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note&lt;/strong&gt;: Meeting dates are subject to change. Please check for notices of cancellations, postponements, or schedule changes below.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Mayor and Council</title>
      <link>http://localhost:49902/government/mayor-council/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 01 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:49902/government/mayor-council/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Meet the dedicated individuals who serve as your elected representatives on the Village of Consort Council. Our Mayor and Councillors are committed to making decisions that benefit our community and enhance the quality of life for all residents.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;mayor&#34;&gt;Mayor&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;mayor-name&#34;&gt;[Mayor Name]&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&#34;http://localhost:49902/images/council/mayor.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Mayor Photo&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Term&lt;/strong&gt;: [Year] - [Year]&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;strong&gt;Email&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;a href=&#34;mailto:mayor@consort.ca&#34;&gt;mayor@consort.ca&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&#xA;&lt;strong&gt;Phone&lt;/strong&gt;: [Phone Number]&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;[Mayor biography paragraph - include background, experience, community involvement, vision for Consort, and key priorities. This section should be 2-3 paragraphs highlighting the Mayor&amp;rsquo;s connection to the community and leadership philosophy.]&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Meeting Agendas &amp; Minutes</title>
      <link>http://localhost:49902/government/agendas-minutes/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 01 Jan 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:49902/government/agendas-minutes/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Access current and archived Council meeting agendas and minutes for the Village of Consort. All documents are available for public review in accordance with our commitment to transparent and accountable government.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;about-agendas-and-minutes&#34;&gt;About Agendas and Minutes&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agendas&lt;/strong&gt; outline the items to be discussed at each Council meeting and are posted at least 24 hours in advance of the meeting.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minutes&lt;/strong&gt; provide a record of Council&amp;rsquo;s discussions and decisions. Minutes are approved at the next regular Council meeting before being posted publicly.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
